### Why no `originPath` plumbing
PR #231 used `originPath` because `applyToLeague` returns the user to the originating league page (e.g. `/id/<slug>`), and the popup mounts there. For the join flow, all 4 live actions terminate at `/join/[code]/welcome` — the destination IS the popup-mounting page. A simple query-string append on the existing redirect target is sufficient; no validator wrapper or `safeOriginPath` call is needed because we're not echoing a user-supplied path.

